description: From Middle English inexplicable, from Middle French inexplicable, from Latin inexplicābilis, from in- (“not”) +‎ explicābilis (“explicable”).

adjectives.description: inexplicable (comparative more inexplicable, superlative most inexplicable)

entries.meaning: Impossible to explain; not easily accounted for.
examples: Synonyms: inexplainable, unexplainable, insoluble; see also Thesaurus:incomprehensible
